column1: Measurements made using standards comprising SHORT, OPEN, and 50Ω (actual 50.95Ω), via  a MS147 jack.  Cable data include a push-on female jack.  S22 (jack end) is worse than the S11 (SMA(f) end). Field loads are measured to be 19.6, 62.8 and 194.7Ω.  A priori values were 19.49, 49.99, and 194.65Ω.  Solder cracks formed during transport.
